Class ConcordanceDataStructure

  • java.lang.Object
    • ConcordanceDataStructure
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ConcordanceDataStructureInterface

    public class ConcordanceDataStructure
extends java.lang.Object
implements ConcordanceDataStructureInterface
    This is the Concordance Data Structure Class. It is the data structure class that is used with the Concordance Data Manager class. This is a hash table with buckets. Your hash table with be an array of linked lists of ConcordanceDataElements. Use the hashcode for an ConcordanceDataElement to place in the hashtable. Do not enter duplicate words or duplicate line numbers for a word. There should be two constructors. The first one takes in an integer which represents the estimated number of words in the text. Determine the size of the table by using a loading factor of 1.5 and a 4K+3 prime.
    Author:
    Alex Juan
